headline: Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) Appoints Multiple Co-Lead Underwriters for Fixed-Income Offering
summary: On June 5, 2025, Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) announced the addition of several financial institutions, including Deutsche Bank Securities Inc. and Goldman Sachs & Co. LLC, as Co-Lead Underwriters for its fixed-income offering, suggesting an effort to bolster financial stability. This development comes as the S&P 500 reached 6,000 points for the first time since February, buoyed by a strong May jobs report and easing tariff concerns.
